http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Call-to-uphold-Constitution/article14024417.ece

The 67th Republic Day was celebrated with fanfare by various agencies on Tuesday.Taking salute at the celebrations organised by the district authorities, Thiruvanchoor Radhakrishnan, Minister for Forests and Transport, stressed the need to stand together at a time when the nation was facing challenges from both inside and outside.The country was moving fast to take its rightful position among the nations, he said.The one binding factor that helped India stand together was its Constitution which ensured equal rights and opportunity to all, he added, making it clear that it was the duty of every citizen to uphold the Constitution.District Collector U.V. Jose, Police Chief Satheesh Bino, district panchayat president Joshy Philip, municipal chairperson P.R. Sona, other district officials, local body representatives and others participated.